00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:25.000
Specific factors are less mobile, and often not mobile at all, because they imply some special knowledge, special methods of economic activity. Accordingly, in the international economy, such a division into general and specific factors is due to the fact that the income of the owners of specific and general factors is different.

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:52.000
If, for example, the economic sector is developing, focusing on export, and in these sectors people begin to receive higher incomes, then, of course, the owners of specific factors, namely, for example, those oil wells, will receive much higher incomes than the owners of general factors, namely, engineers, those who do not have any special qualifications,

