00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:24.000
Special attention is paid to the development of the single, inter-company division of labor, because international transnational corporations organize the production process in such a way that the entire production cycle is not organized in one country, but is distributed in a number of countries, depending on where the production factors are cheaper.

00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:36.000
Thus, the modern international division of labor at the level of the single can be represented in such forms as detailed and operational.

00:12:36.000 --> 00:13:01.000
Imagine, the technology of production of ready-made clothes in the United States is being developed, and in adjacent countries, border areas, for example, clothes are made in the open, and in another country, clothes are made by sewing sleeves and pockets, or buttons. Thus, companies highlight the most rational solutions to these problems.

00:13:01.000 --> 00:13:22.000
