The next form of developing international economic relations

01:55:00.000 --> 01:55:03.000
is the loans of international organizations.

01:55:03.000 --> 01:55:07.000
The goals of these organizations are somewhat different from those loans,

01:55:07.000 --> 01:55:10.000
which, for example, commercial banks represent.

01:55:10.000 --> 01:55:16.000
Why? Because their main task is to stabilize the economic situation of developed countries.

01:55:16.000 --> 01:55:21.000
And therefore, such international organizations as the International Monetary Fund

01:55:21.000 --> 01:55:23.000
and the World Bank,

01:55:23.000 --> 01:55:30.000
by the way, the World Bank and the IMF are the structures of the United Nations.

01:55:30.000 --> 01:55:34.000
These structures, their goal is not to make profits,

01:55:34.000 --> 01:55:37.000
so usually the interest on these loans,

01:55:37.000 --> 01:55:40.000
although they are also required to be paid,

01:55:40.000 --> 01:55:44.000
is quite low, and they provide long-term loans

01:55:44.000 --> 01:55:49.000
for financing economic programs and certain targeted projects.

01:55:50.000 --> 01:55:55.000
In particular, the last loan that Russia received,

01:55:55.000 --> 01:55:58.000
well, Russia received it in the near future,

01:55:58.000 --> 01:56:01.000
was a targeted program for the World Bank,

01:56:01.000 --> 01:56:06.000
related to the development of research and the fight against the SPYD.

01:56:06.000 --> 01:56:11.000
International and regional banks are also organizations

01:56:11.000 --> 01:56:18.000
that set about the same goals as the International Monetary Fund and the World Bank.

01:56:18.000 --> 01:56:23.000
These are European, Asian, African and Inter-American development banks.

01:56:23.000 --> 01:56:25.000
They have the name of such a development bank.

01:56:25.000 --> 01:56:32.000
Therefore, they support social and economic projects within their continents.

01:56:32.000 --> 01:56:37.000
The development of international loans leads to such a situation

01:56:37.000 --> 01:56:42.000
that in the end many countries begin to live in debt.

01:56:42.000 --> 01:56:44.000
Economists even have a term,

01:56:44.000 --> 01:56:48.000
the term of international economists is the debt economy.

01:56:48.000 --> 01:56:52.000
But the situation for different countries is different.

01:56:52.000 --> 01:56:57.000
On the one hand, the US debt economy, for example,

01:56:57.000 --> 01:57:04.000
even received its name in the textbooks of the international economy

01:57:04.000 --> 01:57:07.000
as the deficit of the payment balance without tears,

01:57:07.000 --> 01:57:09.000
that is, debts without tears.

01:57:09.000 --> 01:57:10.000
Look at the diagram.

01:57:10.000 --> 01:57:16.000
The US foreign debt in the first quarter of 2006

01:57:16.000 --> 01:57:21.000
has already reached more than $10 trillion.

01:57:21.000 --> 01:57:26.000
But in this case, it did not have such a sharp impact

01:57:26.000 --> 01:57:30.000
on the fall of the US currency rate, for example,

01:57:30.000 --> 01:57:34.000
or on any other macroeconomic indicators.

01:57:34.000 --> 01:57:38.000
But the Indian foreign debt, for comparison, is only $140 billion.

01:57:38.000 --> 01:57:41.000
If you remember, I already mentioned the number 140.

01:57:41.000 --> 01:57:46.000
It was once, for example, the value of our Russian foreign debt to the USSR.

01:57:46.000 --> 01:57:48.000
For us, it was a very difficult time,

01:57:48.000 --> 01:57:52.000
because you need to pay not only debts, but also interest on them.

01:57:52.000 --> 01:57:58.000
But the foreign debt of Ukraine is not comparable at all to these indicators.

01:57:58.000 --> 01:58:00.000
It's only $50 billion.

01:58:00.000 --> 01:58:03.000
But the pace and volume of Ukraine's development is such

01:58:03.000 --> 01:58:09.000
that, of course, further involvement in international debt,

01:58:09.000 --> 01:58:14.000
these debt obligations, can ultimately lead to the development of Ukraine.

01:58:14.000 --> 01:58:19.000
Therefore, the idea of ​​the debt economy is such

01:58:19.000 --> 01:58:25.000
that, of course, if you have, in principle, a fairly high economic potential,

01:58:25.000 --> 01:58:27.000
and you have accumulated it,

01:58:27.000 --> 01:58:32.000
and you have the opportunity to develop your economy in some medium-term plan,

01:58:32.000 --> 01:58:34.000
and pay off your debts,

01:58:34.000 --> 01:58:39.000
then living in debt for some time is not so dangerous,

01:58:39.000 --> 01:58:41.000
including even for the budget.

01:58:41.000 --> 01:58:46.000
But if it is a transitional economy, or, moreover, a developing country,

01:58:46.000 --> 01:58:53.000
and the world market is not in favor of exporting this developing country,

01:58:53.000 --> 01:58:56.000
then the option of the debt economy is dangerous.

01:58:56.000 --> 01:59:00.000
Let's remember 1998.

01:59:00.000 --> 01:59:03.000
The financial crisis that occurred in Russia at that time

01:59:03.000 --> 01:59:08.000
was not only related to the operations with securities,

01:59:08.000 --> 01:59:12.000
with the pyramids that the Central Bank and, accordingly,

01:59:12.000 --> 01:59:16.000
commercial banks carried out on the GKO-FZ, on securities.

01:59:16.000 --> 01:59:21.000
It was also connected with the drop in prices in the world market

01:59:21.000 --> 01:59:25.000
for the raw materials that Russia exports.

01:59:25.000 --> 01:59:30.000
Namely, the sharp drop in steel prices and the sharp drop in oil prices.

01:59:30.000 --> 01:59:36.000
In this version, our debt economy could not cope, could not stand it,

01:59:36.000 --> 01:59:41.000
and could not pay off its debts on its own,

01:59:41.000 --> 01:59:44.000
and had to undergo a long procedure of settlement

01:59:44.000 --> 01:59:48.000
in order to, in the end, restructurize the Russian debt.

01:59:48.000 --> 01:59:52.000
But as soon as oil and metal prices went up,

01:59:52.000 --> 01:59:57.000
Russia created favorable conditions for paying off its external debts.

01:59:57.000 --> 02:00:01.000
Thus, the debt economy for a large, developed country

02:00:01.000 --> 02:00:04.000
is really a variant of a deficit without tears.

02:00:04.000 --> 02:00:10.000
Moreover, it should be remembered that the US dollar is a currency

02:00:10.000 --> 02:00:15.000
that is in the reserves of most countries in the world.

02:00:15.000 --> 02:00:19.000
That is, it is used by international investment and banking demand.

02:00:19.000 --> 02:00:24.000
Based on this, even direct repayment of one's debts

02:00:24.000 --> 02:00:27.000
by turning on the printing press

02:00:27.000 --> 02:00:32.000
can be avoided for some time without terrible consequences

02:00:32.000 --> 02:00:36.000
for the national economy and for the entire world community.

02:00:36.000 --> 02:00:41.000
Nevertheless, such a deficit also requires

02:00:41.000 --> 02:00:44.000
a certain management and thoughtful decisions.

02:00:44.000 --> 02:00:49.000
An example is the 1970s, when the US,

02:00:49.000 --> 02:00:55.000
starting in the 1960s, was solving its social and economic problems

02:00:55.000 --> 02:00:58.000
due to the dollar rebound.

02:00:58.000 --> 02:01:02.000
And in the end, the bought-up euro-dollars in Europe

02:01:02.000 --> 02:01:07.000
plus the rise in oil prices

02:01:07.000 --> 02:01:11.000
led to the Bretton Woods crisis

02:01:11.000 --> 02:01:14.000
and the collapse of the US dollar

02:01:14.000 --> 02:01:18.000
and, accordingly, the crisis in this large and stable economy.

02:01:18.000 --> 02:01:21.000
But a stable large economy

02:01:21.000 --> 02:01:24.000
comes out of such a terrible situation faster.

02:01:24.000 --> 02:01:29.000
And if, for example, in the 1970s the US was in a crisis,

02:01:29.000 --> 02:01:32.000
then literally within 90 years

02:01:32.000 --> 02:01:35.000
the stable rates of economic growth of about 4%

02:01:35.000 --> 02:01:37.000
were held for quite a long time.

02:01:37.000 --> 02:01:41.000
That is, a large economy, of course, has more potential.

02:01:41.000 --> 02:01:45.000
And, accordingly, there is a greater chance

02:01:45.000 --> 02:01:48.000
for a large developed country to live in debt

02:01:48.000 --> 02:01:51.000
and be such a deficit economy.

