The next group of relations is associated with such a form of international economic relations as capital withdrawal.

02:02:56.000 --> 02:03:04.000
What are the factors of capital withdrawal and why is it intensified?

02:03:04.000 --> 02:03:11.000
If we take the rate of economic growth, then, as I said, the rate of foreign trade is higher than the rate of economic growth.

02:03:11.000 --> 02:03:18.000
So the rate of capital withdrawal is higher than the rate of foreign trade and higher than the rate of economic growth.

02:03:18.000 --> 02:03:23.000
The first reason is, of course, the development of the global market.

02:03:23.000 --> 02:03:35.000
Since the withdrawal of capital occurs in different forms, including in conjunction with the organization of foreign production, then, of course, the development of the global market will help with the withdrawal of capital.

02:03:35.000 --> 02:03:49.000
The concentration and centralization of capital in national economies leads to the fact that it does not find a worthy profitable application of national territories and, again, goes beyond the country.

02:03:49.000 --> 02:03:58.000
Accordingly, the accumulation of ship capital of industrially developed countries, again, contributes to the export of capital.

02:03:58.000 --> 02:04:06.000
And on the other hand, there is also an interest of certain countries in the influx of foreign capital.

02:04:06.000 --> 02:04:18.000
Because, if you remember, the most developing export-oriented countries are just interested in the influx of foreign capital and foreign technologies.

02:04:18.000 --> 02:04:24.000
The next reason for the withdrawal of capital is the overcoming of protectionist barriers.

02:04:24.000 --> 02:04:38.000
If we have a fairly rigid system in the country on some commodity nomenclature, on some kind of commodity production, import, how can we bypass this obstacle?

02:04:38.000 --> 02:04:47.000
We can organize the assembly on the territory of a given country. And this is the withdrawal of capital, the process of organizing direct investments.

02:04:47.000 --> 02:04:51.000
A vivid example of this is the Russian car industry.

02:04:52.000 --> 02:05:08.000
Despite the high import barriers on the tariffs for import of foreign foreign products, especially, so to speak, young people, it is just limited.

02:05:08.000 --> 02:05:21.000
This tariff is reduced by the fact that many Western firms organized assembly production on the basis of those machine-building car factories that already existed in Russia.

02:05:21.000 --> 02:05:31.000
The next reason for the withdrawal of capital is that it is associated with the development of transnational corporations and transnational banks.

02:05:31.000 --> 02:05:34.000
Another factor is the military-political aspects.

02:05:34.000 --> 02:05:46.000
In principle, the country, including, for example, the United States, is organized by withdrawing capital, organizing economic assistance or with the help of its own transnational corporations.

02:05:46.000 --> 02:05:50.000
In fact, it spreads not only economic, but also political influence.

02:05:50.000 --> 02:05:57.000
And in this regard, the donor country is interested in the withdrawal of capital to other countries.

02:05:57.000 --> 02:06:08.000
And the last factor is that all countries of the world understand what military-political significance the country that organizes its foreign production acquires.

02:06:08.000 --> 02:06:20.000
These governments develop a whole system of measures for state support, both for export of capital and for import.

02:06:21.000 --> 02:06:31.000
Accordingly, if the country is in a crisis situation and needs development assistance, it will be state support for foreign investments in the territory of its country.

02:06:31.000 --> 02:06:41.000
The main forms of capital withdrawal are both direct investments and capital withdrawal in the form of ship capital.

02:06:42.000 --> 02:06:49.000
The disadvantages of ship capital are due to the fact that it is invested in securities.

02:06:49.000 --> 02:07:03.000
And, accordingly, as soon as the conventure on the stock market, on the securities market, changes, then the owners of these securities, when they are cheapened, immediately try to get rid of them.

02:07:04.000 --> 02:07:12.000
And, in general, depending on how they play within their speculative attacks on the increase or decrease in the value of securities,

02:07:12.000 --> 02:07:22.000
ship capital in the form of the capital in the form of securities, in portfolio investments, is quite mobile.

02:07:22.000 --> 02:07:31.000
That is, it has absolute mobility, and in case of what, there is a flow of hot money from the country that was counting on investing its economy.

02:07:32.000 --> 02:07:42.000
Therefore, of course, direct investments are less mobile, and they are beneficial to the country, because the companies that organize direct investments,

02:07:42.000 --> 02:07:49.000
they are forced to organize, to be responsible for the production process that they organized in this territory.

02:07:49.000 --> 02:07:57.000
And so, to get rid of the market and leave this country, they will need some time.

02:07:58.000 --> 02:08:09.000
That is, practically, the investment in the form of direct investments, the only way such capital can go is to sell their factories, which they have already created in this foreign country.

02:08:09.000 --> 02:08:15.000
And, in general, it turns out that the result of their activities remains in the national economy.

02:08:15.000 --> 02:08:20.000
Therefore, all countries, when they show statistics of international investments,

02:08:20.000 --> 02:08:28.000
