In the broad sense of the word, the currency is any commodity that is able to perform the function of money.

04:35:15.000 --> 04:35:26.000
As you know, economic theory proposes a number of functions of money. These are the measure of value, means of circulation, means of payment, means of accumulation, and world money.

04:35:27.000 --> 04:35:39.000
In modern terms, almost no currency performs the function of world money, that is, such funds that would be recognized for the exchange, for payments by all states.

04:35:39.000 --> 04:35:50.000
But nevertheless, we can say that in the modern currency system, the rest of the functions of national currencies are being performed.

04:35:50.000 --> 04:36:05.000
And the currency in the international exchange, in the international arena, should provide international commodity flows, as well as work on the international credit and fund market.

04:36:05.000 --> 04:36:19.000
The currency can be classified by its affiliation. If you ask a citizen what a currency is, he will say a dollar or a euro. In this case, this term applies to a foreign currency.

04:36:19.000 --> 04:36:42.000
Therefore, it is a payment method of other countries that is legally or illegally used in the territory of the domestic country. At the same time, the national currency must be allocated, that is, the legal payment method on the territory of the issuing country that provides the exchange of goods.

04:36:42.000 --> 04:36:55.000
And now we will talk about the possibility of currency regulation of the national currency.

04:36:55.000 --> 04:37:10.000
In principle, the following characteristics of the reserve currency, freely convertible, and the hard currency can be identified. All these characteristics apply to various national currencies of the countries of the world.

04:37:10.000 --> 04:37:30.000
Of course, a separate national currency may not have these characteristics. But any national currency, and accordingly, those currency bodies that try to regulate the currency relations, try to develop their system to such an extent that the national currency becomes both a reserve, a freely convertible, and a hard one.

04:37:30.000 --> 04:37:52.000
Let's look more closely at the definition. So, the reserve currency is a foreign currency that the national economy accumulates to maintain its currency reserves.

04:37:52.000 --> 04:38:12.000
And accordingly, if the country is in a situation of a deficit of payments, in particular, on the foreign trade balance, then in this case, the central bank can cover the negative balance of the payment balance from the currency reserves.

04:38:12.000 --> 04:38:27.000
Of course, the reserve currency is a currency that should have the following properties in our list, namely, it should be freely convertible and hard. So what is a freely convertible currency?

04:38:27.000 --> 04:38:40.000
It is a currency that is widely used to make international payments, is actively sold and bought, and is recognized by all players of the international currency market.

04:38:40.000 --> 04:38:50.000
This definition is, of course, the most general for the concept of a freely convertible currency. We will further analyze the criteria for convertibility.

04:38:50.000 --> 04:39:01.000
A hard currency. In this case, a hard currency is the basis of a reserve currency, and, in general, a hard currency is accumulated in reserve funds.

04:39:01.000 --> 04:39:21.000
This currency is characterized by a stable currency exchange rate, it is less subject to financial risks, and in this case it is assumed that a hard currency is organized and formed only in those countries where internal economic stability is the main feature of economic development.

04:39:21.000 --> 04:39:41.000
So, a hard currency is formed when the internal economy is stable, when foreign trade flows are stable, and the trend of economic development has positive results in all macroeconomic indicators.

04:39:41.000 --> 04:39:59.000
