04:39:59.000 --> 04:40:11.000
As you can see, it is assumed that we are talking about converting our own national currency, and it is its ability to exchange foreign currency that is understood in the concept of convertibility.

04:40:11.000 --> 04:40:31.000
In this case, the definition of a resident and a non-resident is in force. The most accurate definition of a resident is given by economic statistics. If these are individuals, then these are citizens of a country that has been in their territory for more than six months.

04:40:31.000 --> 04:40:47.000
Residents are legal entities since the registration of a legal entity. Therefore, as soon as a company is registered in the territory of this country, it is a resident.

04:40:47.000 --> 04:40:58.000
In this case, it is assumed that residents and non-residents freely exchange national currency and use it in their trade and financial transactions.

04:40:58.000 --> 04:41:20.000
In order to understand the principles of currency convertibility according to such two significant characteristics as the convertibility of the currency on current accounts and the convertibility of the currency on the account of capital, we need to look at the payment balance scheme.

04:41:20.000 --> 04:41:42.000
Let's look at the payment balance scheme. The payment balance consists of two large accounts. The first article in the current operations account calculates export and import. The difference between export and import is determined as the trade balance of the country.

04:41:42.000 --> 04:41:56.000
Naturally, if the export in the country is greater than the import, then the trade balance is positive. The second article of the payment balance is the income obtained from abroad and the income paid abroad.

04:41:56.000 --> 04:42:09.000
The income is obtained from the factors of production. The transfer of wages, interest, and profits associated with foreign economic activity is included in the current operations account.

04:42:09.000 --> 04:42:33.000
The last component of the current operations account is the current private transfers obtained from abroad or paid abroad. In this case, such transfers are assumed to be various donations, assistance, which is provided by private organizations, not the state.

04:42:33.000 --> 04:43:02.000
If we now sum up the indicators of the left and right columns presented in our scheme and find the difference between them, then the balance of the current operations accounts allows us to take into account mainly foreign trade flows and the flows of income of the owners of the factors of production, which are organized in international economic relations.

04:43:02.000 --> 04:43:16.000
The capital account or the capital operations account, first of all, the first component of the capital account is foreign investment and domestic investment, which we transfer abroad.

04:43:16.000 --> 04:43:33.000
As is well known, investments can be both portfolio and direct, but nevertheless, in this case, it does not matter, they can be divided into accounts, but we have all these investment financial flows in the first line of the capital account.

04:43:33.000 --> 04:43:54.000
The second line is the inflow of state foreign transfers. Here is the state aid, the inflow and outflow of foreign aid provided by state institutions, reflected in the capital account as an indicator of state foreign transfers.

04:43:55.000 --> 04:44:06.000
Accordingly, in addition to donations or such free financial assistance as transfers, another component of the financial flows between countries is loans.

04:44:06.000 --> 04:44:19.000
The next line of the capital account is the inflow of loans to the country and the outflow of loans from the country. The balance of the capital account balances the left and right columns of the account.

04:44:19.000 --> 04:44:40.000
It is assumed that there is a certain interdependence between the balance of the trade balance and the balance of the capital account. The total balance is calculated as the amount on the balance of the trade balance and as the balance of the capital account.

04:44:40.000 --> 04:44:56.000
Please note that in this case, both the trade balance, the balance of the current operations, and the balance of the capital are quite interconnected.

04:44:56.000 --> 04:45:11.000
If international trade develops in the country, there is a fairly rapid flow of exports, then usually a positive trade balance and a positive balance of the current operations are formed.

04:45:11.000 --> 04:45:30.000
Then the state in the country, economic agents accumulate excess capital assets. And then such a country usually gives a loan, carries out foreign transfers abroad, carries out international investments.

04:45:30.000 --> 04:45:51.000
Thus, it turns out that the balance of the capital is the balancing factor of the balance of the current operations. And if we have a positive balance of the current operations, then there is an inflow to the country on payments, on trade transactions, then usually the capital account is outflow of foreign investments.

04:45:52.000 --> 04:46:05.000
Thus, the capital account will have a negative value. Plus and minus in the general arithmetic addition, in this case, give zero. That is, if the balance of payments is balanced, then it is zero.

04:46:05.000 --> 04:46:20.000
If the situation is such that foreign trade is less developed, import is large enough, and exporters are not so competitive on the international market, then the balance of the current operations becomes negative.

04:46:20.000 --> 04:46:35.000
In order to cover these external economic payments, the state and the companies have to make loans. And then the capital account balances the negative account of the current operations.

04:46:35.000 --> 04:46:50.000
And according to the indicators of the capital account, the inflow of capital assets to the country becomes positive. Thus, the first and second halves of the balance of payments are mutually balanced articles.

04:46:50.000 --> 04:47:08.000
If the situation is such that it is impossible to cover the country's shortcomings of the current operations due to loans and other investment inflows, then reserve funds are used.

04:47:08.000 --> 04:47:23.000
Then the reserve fund performs the function of a source from which the central bank covers its external debts.

04:47:23.000 --> 04:47:44.000
Based on this, we can find out the convertibility of the current operations, that is, the absence of restrictions on payments and transfers.

04:47:45.000 --> 04:48:07.000
Accordingly, it can be hard and soft. If we have a fixed currency exchange rate, then the convertibility of the current operations is hard. If we have a floating currency exchange rate or a rate with regulated floating, then the convertibility of the current operations is soft.

04:48:07.000 --> 04:48:22.000
First of all, when entering the International Monetary Fund, countries must introduce convertibility of the current operations for their currencies to support the development of international trade relations.

04:48:22.000 --> 04:48:48.000
There are many factors that affect the convertibility of the current currency. But, as I said in the previous lectures, internal and external economic development certainly affects the convertibility of the current currency.

04:48:48.000 --> 04:49:16.000
If we have a liberal trade system, and, accordingly, the economic barriers that restrain export and import are low enough, then the rapid development of export and import leads to the stabilization of the national economy and economic growth, and, accordingly, to a positive trade and payment balance.

04:49:16.000 --> 04:49:36.000
Foreign currency inflow occurs. At the same time, there is a rise in demand for domestic currency, since we export our goods, and they can be paid from the exchange rate of foreign currency for domestic currency.

04:49:36.000 --> 04:49:58.000
And most importantly, there is an internal demand for the economy, and this demand turns into a demand for domestic national currency. Then the exchange rate becomes stable and, of course, its convertibility increases.

04:49:58.000 --> 04:50:22.000
Convertibility of capital operations. There is a lack of restrictions on payments and transfers on the account of capital, which we have previously considered. This implies that the currency is convertible for such operations as direct portfolio investments, loans, capital grants.

04:50:22.000 --> 04:50:42.000
The demand for the International Monetary Fund is not distributed for convertibility of capital operations. Moreover, depending on the financial and economic situation on the domestic market, one or another developed country introduces restrictions on convertibility of capital operations.

04:50:42.000 --> 04:51:08.000
And even though the US dollar is a solid, convertible, stable currency, at a certain time the US government introduced restrictions on convertibility of capital operations. This was in the 1970s, when the world financial crisis was taking place.

04:51:08.000 --> 04:51:34.000
What are the most typical capital limitations? First of all, this is a limitation of direct foreign investment in a separate sector. The state prohibits foreign economic agents to invest or buy shares of strategic enterprises.

04:51:34.000 --> 04:51:57.000
Then there is a ban on opening accounts of foreign currency in foreign banks. The next limitation is the requirement of a return on profit by national companies investing abroad. This requirement usually arises when the national currency exchange rate of the country is experiencing difficulties.

04:51:58.000 --> 04:52:25.000
The demand to issue or sell foreign currency obtained abroad was introduced by the Central Bank for a long time. In the current conditions, when the positive balance of trade and payment is the main positive feature of the Russian economy, this demand is certainly removed.

04:52:25.000 --> 04:52:53.000
The next limitation is the ban on buying foreign securities by residents of the country. This is a limitation on the current stage of Russia's development.

04:52:53.000 --> 04:53:19.000
The next limitation is the introduction of foreign loans. In general, the form of capital limitation is quite diverse. Depending on how quickly the country moves towards full convertibility of its currency, it removes certain restrictions.

04:53:20.000 --> 04:53:45.000
The general principle is that if the convertibility of the capital is limited, then there is no outflow of capital. Naturally, such a form of limitation will be used primarily by the transition economy or developing countries or countries that experience problems in the national cyclical development of the economy.

04:53:46.000 --> 04:53:56.000
Full convertibility assumes that there are no restrictions, no control, both on the account of the current and on the account of capital operations.

04:53:57.000 --> 04:54:22.000
Russia is experiencing a difficult path to convertibility of the ruble. In the programs of Russia's development for the next three years, the Central Bank is tasked with bringing Russia to full convertibility of the ruble.

04:54:22.000 --> 04:54:28.000
For this purpose, the currency liberalization is carried out step by step. That is, certain restrictions are removed.

04:54:28.000 --> 04:54:54.000
In particular, one of the options that prompts the recognition of the weightiness of the convertibility of the ruble is the law introduced by the Central Bank on January 1, 2007, according to which our domestic exporters pay taxes to the budget in the domestic currency.

04:54:54.000 --> 04:55:03.000
This stimulates the exchange of dollars and euros for the Russian ruble and the demand for the domestic currency increases. Its stability is established.

