What are the conditions for the transition to full convertibility of the national currency? Let's summarize.

04:55:43.000 --> 04:55:52.000
This is a difficult issue for the government, because the convertibility of the currency primarily implies the stabilization of the country's economic development.

04:55:52.000 --> 04:56:06.000
Internal macroeconomic stability is minimal inflation, almost minimal unemployment, stable economic growth within 2-5%.

04:56:06.000 --> 04:56:15.000
This is a stable state budget. It is assumed that the state budget has not deficits, but profits.

04:56:15.000 --> 04:56:30.000
The central bank monitors and adopts various levers of the credit-money policy to stabilize the currency.

04:56:30.000 --> 04:56:43.000
In general, all these conditions for the transition to full convertibility of the national currency are already being implemented in the development of the national economy of Russia.

04:56:43.000 --> 04:57:03.000
