05:00:06.000 --> 05:00:25.000
As you can see, this is the internal convertibility that occurs when the economy is unstable. It is assumed that internal convertibility is the freedom of citizens to accumulate their savings in one or another currency.

05:00:25.000 --> 05:00:45.000
As soon as the Russian ruble became more stable in its development, a reverse trend occurred. According to the modern assessment of the Central Bank of Russia, there is a shift in the preferences of Russian investors.

05:00:45.000 --> 05:00:59.000
Current accounts are opened in rubles, while the savings in dollars or euros grow at a slower pace.

05:00:59.000 --> 05:01:16.000
In modern conditions, the main feature of the internal convertibility of the Russian ruble is the right of Russian citizens to open foreign currency accounts in euros, dollars, and in various national banks.

05:01:16.000 --> 05:01:32.000
