05:13:33.000 --> 05:13:58.000
So, the parity of purchasing power implies such a calculation exchange rate, which is really called a real exchange rate, because it takes into account the level of inflation in foreign countries and in the domestic country. Thus, the most clearly, unlike the market exchange rate, which is influenced by demand and supply, shows the real purchasing power of the country.

05:13:58.000 --> 05:14:18.000
In particular, according to the parity of purchasing power, the exchange rate of Russia should be not about 25 rubles per dollar, but only 15. That is, the purchasing power is strong enough due to the fact that we have a high export, although recently there has been a high import.

05:14:18.000 --> 05:14:44.000
The parity of purchasing power is calculated by different methods, as I said, through comparable baskets of goods. It is clear that these should not be goods of some local consumption, which are not connected with international preferences. This is just the product group that is used in any country.

05:14:44.000 --> 05:15:04.000
The simplest example is the setting of a parity for some one product that is widespread all over the world. In this regard, McDonald's can be proud that one of the options for calculating the parity of purchasing power, though the most approximate, is the ratio of prices of hamburgers in different countries.

05:15:04.000 --> 05:15:30.000
Depending on the ratio of prices, you can calculate the most correct, more adequate currency exchange rate or real exchange rate. In statistics, the Central Bank, of course, calculates the parity of purchasing power of the currency by more complex methods, as I said, through the price index.

05:15:30.000 --> 05:15:40.000
Thus, it takes into account the necessary changes in inflation in its country and abroad.

05:16:00.000 --> 05:16:28.000
The most ancient standard was the metal standard, that is, the gold, silver and so on. In principle, the gold standard was introduced twice in the 20th century, that is, before the war and for a short time in some countries after the war.

05:16:28.000 --> 05:16:44.000
