05:20:02.000 --> 05:20:28.000
The next component of the currency system is the currency regime. Depending on how developed the country is, what types of internal economic policy it carries out, one country or another adheres to various options for the flexibility of the currency rate.

05:20:28.000 --> 05:20:48.000
We can consider three options for the flexibility of the currency rate. The most extreme option is the hard-fixed currency rate. The other opposite side of the currency flexibility is the free-floating currency rate, the ideal floating rate.

05:20:48.000 --> 05:21:12.000
And in the meantime, the regulated floating rate, which in the 70s was termed dirty floating, i.e. floating related to the state interventions of the Central Bank on the currency market, with the purchase and sale of currency and, accordingly, the maintenance of one or another measure of their domestic currency.

05:21:12.000 --> 05:21:26.000
The hard-fixed currency rate, although it seems that countries in the modern world should abandon it, nevertheless, it has certain advantages, which we will talk about later.

05:21:42.000 --> 05:21:56.000
But in the ideal, the currency rate should rise, because the purity of the purchasing power is much higher, because China is now leading us in terms of foreign trade, in terms of the pace of foreign trade in the world.

05:21:56.000 --> 05:22:22.000
The options for the floating currency rate are the fixed currency rate, which automatically changes depending on the macroeconomic indicators listed in the legislation, for example, the level of inflation or the payment balance of the country.

05:22:23.000 --> 05:22:37.000
The next direction is the regulated floating currency rate. How does the state manage this floating rate? This is not an automatic change.

05:22:37.000 --> 05:22:57.000
It is assumed that the Central Bank in this case makes a decision to change the currency rate by means of intervention on the currency market. I repeat, the purchase and sale of the same currency, as a result of which the currency rate of the country must be somehow corrected.

05:22:57.000 --> 05:23:14.000
And the last option of the floating currency rate is the independent floating rate without the intervention of the state. The question arises, is it not an independent floating rate, such an ideal option of the floating currency rate as a perfect competition?

05:23:14.000 --> 05:23:40.000
No, the independent floating currency rate in such a system is periodically used by countries when they have a crisis in the national financial system. And in order to find out at what level the currency rate becomes more or less, and then to correct it, maybe to implement a policy of maintaining this currency rate,

05:23:41.000 --> 05:24:01.000
the mechanism of non-interference of the state and the independent floating rate is included. In particular, in the 1970s, at the time of the financial currency crisis, European countries completely released their currency rates for 1-2 months to somehow navigate the currency space.

05:24:01.000 --> 05:24:22.000
What are the modern ways to fix the currency rate? The most common is the fixation of one currency, but nevertheless, many countries fix the currency rate according to the value of the currency basket.

05:24:22.000 --> 05:24:42.000
For example, modern Belarus fixes its currency rate in the basket of solid currencies of the dollar and euro, but also to the currency of neighboring countries, that is, Poland, Lithuania, Latvia, Ukraine. And since September 1, 2000, the Russian ruble has been included in the fixation basket according to the decision of the Central Bank of Belarus.

05:24:42.000 --> 05:25:05.000
Traditionally, when fixing the currency rate according to the value of the currency basket, the most stable partners in international trade and currency-financial relations are used.

05:25:06.000 --> 05:25:33.000
In history, when the EU did not yet have a single currency, many developing countries, former colonies of European countries, just fixed their currency rates to the former metropolis, for example, to the French franc or to the German mark.

05:25:33.000 --> 05:25:43.000
This trend has been preserved to a certain extent for them, because they now fix their currency rate to the euro.

05:25:43.000 --> 05:26:04.000
The soft form of currency rate fixing is the currency corridor. This is also an option for regulated floating, but it is assumed that the Central Bank of Belarus announces in advance at what intervals, at what limits the currency rate will fluctuate.

05:26:04.000 --> 05:26:25.000
The fixed currency rate is also subject to the possibility of a certain deviation. Why? Because, in the end, there is a free supply and demand currency market, and the influence of supply and demand can make the market currency rate deviate from the fixed currency rate.

05:26:26.000 --> 05:26:53.000
And so, in order not to affect the stability of the national currency, the Central Bank of Belarus allows a deviation of 1.5% to 2.5% at the fixed currency rate. As soon as the fluctuations reach the limit of 1.5%, the Central Bank of Belarus carries out an intervention and corrects the currency rate.

05:26:53.000 --> 05:27:22.000
If the Central Bank of Belarus did not have enough funds for conversion, then a devaluation of the currency rate occurs, that is, it decreases. Or, on the contrary, if the global market tendency is such that the currency should be stronger, a revaluation occurs, as it was in the 20th century with the Japanese yen, when they could not support a lower currency rate with the resources of their Central Bank.

05:27:22.000 --> 05:27:34.000
Let's return to the currency corridor. The regulated floating within the framework of the currency corridor already suggests fluctuations of more than 2-3%.

05:27:34.000 --> 05:28:01.000
In Russia, until 1998, there was a currency corridor, and the width of the currency corridor was 15%. Somewhere in 1996-1997, just before the currency crisis, it was slightly reduced to 13%, but in general, they could not completely contain the fluctuations of the currency rate.

05:28:04.000 --> 05:28:21.000
If we talk about the currency corridor used in the 1970s, then there was a rather interesting situation when the currency corridor was generally called a snake in the tunnel.

05:28:21.000 --> 05:28:46.000
Because the top and bottom levels of this tunnel were determined by European countries by the sum of the top level, that is, in this case, the cheapest currency rate, the sum of the lowest currency rates and the bottom level, that is, the strong currency rate when fluctuating the currency rate, by the group of the strongest currencies of the European Union.

05:28:46.000 --> 05:29:11.000
But again, such a currency corridor option was managed to keep for the EU for only a few months. Accordingly, the EU currency system came to the conclusion that it was necessary to simply release the currency rates and support them at the expense of the intervention of the Central Bank without the announcement of the currency corridor.

05:29:11.000 --> 05:29:35.000
What is the situation in the modern currency system in Russia? In Russia, there is a floating currency rate, but this is again a regular floating. The currency corridor has already been canceled, since the Russian ruble has become more stable and is subject to less fluctuations.

05:29:35.000 --> 05:29:55.000
The second reason for stabilization is the huge inflow of oil dollars or euro-currencies that flow into the Russian financial territory due to the price increase in oil and energy.

05:29:55.000 --> 05:30:23.000
When the current currency rate of the Russian ruble is determined in modern conditions, it is not used by the quadra system, that is, the system that I have already mentioned, when we have euro, dollar, yen and pound sterling in our currency reserves, but is used for current calculations of the bivalutic basket, that is, euro and dollar.

05:30:23.000 --> 05:30:38.000
60% of the calculations are made in dollars, and, accordingly, the fluctuation of the dollar-USA rate is taken into account, 40% of the bivalutic basket is taken into account by the euro fluctuation.

