05:36:13.000 --> 05:36:26.000
Accordingly, what should the central bank do if it is trying to correct the exchange rate that has been established?

05:36:26.000 --> 05:36:51.000
If the central bank believes that the exchange rate for the dollar is too high and such an expensive Russian currency does not meet the demand of exporters, then the central bank of Russia will intervene, throw rubles into the market and buy dollars.

05:36:51.000 --> 05:37:11.000
Thus, the exchange rate of the ruble begins to decline. If the opposite situation arises, the ruble is too cheap, which can eventually affect inflation in the long term, then the opposite situation of intervention of the central bank of Russia will occur.

