What are the preferences of the currency regimes, depending on how developed the country is?

05:37:38.000 --> 05:37:55.000
If these are economically developed countries, then they are not afraid of the floating currency rate, although ideal floating, as I said, can be found quite rarely and the ideal floating system is usually turned on only when the financial instability.

05:37:55.000 --> 05:38:06.000
But the soft correction of the floating currency rate is the program that is used by all developed countries of the world.

05:38:06.000 --> 05:38:22.000
And through the credit-money monetary policy, the internal macroeconomic stimulation of economic growth is carried out.

05:38:22.000 --> 05:38:38.000
It is not by chance that the proposal for the reconstruction of the Russian economy, which originated from the United States at the end of the 20th century, was associated with monetary-credit-money policy.

05:38:38.000 --> 05:38:56.000
