In order to clarify the scheme of currency damping, we will move on to the next slide, and now pay attention to what other options there are for the influence of the currency rate on foreign trade. This is hidden protectionism.

05:44:28.000 --> 05:44:40.000
In this case, it is assumed that if we have a weak currency rate, then the national consumer will not be able to buy a lot of foreign imports for his cheap money.

05:44:40.000 --> 05:45:02.000
As soon as the national currency rate is increased, then our domestic consumer can buy more equipment, equipment and goods of final consumption for a more valuable ruble.

05:45:02.000 --> 05:45:21.000
Therefore, this option of weakening the currency rate is beneficial to the country if the country tries to implement additional hidden protectionism. This was the situation before 2003 on the Russian market.

05:45:21.000 --> 05:45:46.000
The situation of a weak currency rate led to the fact that we did not have to increase our tariff barriers during this period of time, precisely because the weak ruble automatically, for almost a decade of the end of the 20th century, protected the national economy from the rapid growth of imports.

05:45:46.000 --> 05:46:03.000
But since 2003, this situation has changed, and the reserve of the national economy, in the form of weak ruble protectionism, has ended.

