And now this mechanism does not work, because in the last three years the currency rate of the ruble has stabilized and is slowly growing. And the last unpleasant option of the influence of the currency rate is the Dutch disease.

05:46:21.000 --> 05:46:36.000
What is the situation in the Netherlands? What does the country's financial system suffer from, including the situation of the Dutch disease?

05:46:36.000 --> 05:46:56.000
The name of this situation was given in connection with the situation in the Dutch economy. After the crisis of 1970, which was not only financial, but also associated with a sharp increase in oil prices,

05:46:56.000 --> 05:47:11.000
and the energy crisis, the Netherlands decided to open up the country's internal reserves. A fuel-energy complex began to develop in this country, which was previously in a stagnant state.

05:47:11.000 --> 05:47:31.000
And the financial resources went to this fuel-energy complex. Where did they get it from? Naturally, they came from other sectors of the economy. In this regard, countries suffered, sorry, sectors that worked for internal demand, not for export.

05:47:31.000 --> 05:47:57.000
Moreover, other non-energy sectors suffered. That is, the energy complex was developing at a rapid pace. And the increase in energy prices led to a huge flow of foreign convertible currency to the territory of the Netherlands.

05:47:57.000 --> 05:48:14.000
The Dutch gulden started to grow at that time. Thus, the export prices for Dutch oil, gas and energy products began to rise.

05:48:14.000 --> 05:48:39.000
But the demand for these goods in the world is not so elastic. There is no reaction that if the prices for oil have risen, they are still bought. But the demand for goods that, in addition to energy, the Netherlands exported, was in a crisis situation.

05:48:39.000 --> 05:48:57.000
That is, for such high prices, these goods were not bought. Thus, the Dutch disease hit the structure of the economy twice. The first blow is the withdrawal of resources from other sectors in favor of the export-oriented sector.

05:48:57.000 --> 05:49:20.000
But also within the framework of the export-oriented sector, as a result of the growth of the national currency, the pumping of profits into the energy sector, and, in this case, the loss of other export sectors.

05:49:20.000 --> 05:49:35.000
In addition to the problems with the industry proportions in the country, there are also problems with the currency-financial component of the macroeconomy.

