Based on this, Russia has a strong group of influence on the decrease in the currency exchange rate, primarily exporters.

05:52:28.000 --> 05:52:48.000
But we must not forget that importers are interested in the increase in the currency exchange rate. And not only end-use goods, clothing, food products, but also importers who supply equipment, machines, equipment and technologies to their factories.

05:52:48.000 --> 05:53:00.000
And, of course, the stronger the exchange rate, the more new technologies they can buy in the West. The weaker the exchange rate, the less stable the situation will be and the less preferable for importers.

05:53:00.000 --> 05:53:25.000
So, the struggle of the two forces in any national economy, that is, the interests of exporters and the interests of importers are facing, and depending on this, they affect the government and the currency policy is being developed, which, again, is a kind of compromise between the interests of the domestic economy and the domestic economy oriented to export.

05:53:26.000 --> 05:53:41.000
What are the main factors of the currency exchange rate? Let's summarize. First of all, this is the interest rate on loans. How can the interest rate on loans affect the currency exchange rate?

05:53:41.000 --> 05:54:03.000
