05:54:03.000 --> 05:54:26.000
Based on this, he has a choice. For example, to take and put the currency in which he is going to pay his contracts in the bank, get a percentage and this percentage will cover the currency risks. Therefore, the interest rate on loans abroad and in the national economy will definitely affect the currency exchange rate.

05:54:27.000 --> 05:54:52.000
And take the situation in the United States. Just in the last quarter, the level of the US currency exchange rate rose due to the fact that the central bank of the United States, the so-called Federal Reserve System, raised the interest rate on refinancing, that is, on loans and deposits of their central bank.

05:54:52.000 --> 05:55:21.000
