And if the income of our country is growing, what is the situation? Then our consumers become richer. But they are ready to buy not only domestic goods, but they are also ready to buy imports. Thus, they begin to buy imports, often more than is necessary for the balance of the currency exchange rate, and then it affects as a negative factor on the currency exchange rate.

05:56:12.000 --> 05:56:38.000
Now in Russia, the situation is such that the stabilizing currency exchange rate has forced imports to increase. But so far this situation is not terrible. On the contrary, the increase in imports works as a kind of reference to the decrease in the currency exchange rate.

05:56:38.000 --> 05:56:55.000
Foreign trade policy is also a factor of the currency exchange rate. Because, of course, if we have tariff and other foreign trade barriers, then we will have a limit on the flow of exports and imports, and accordingly a limit on the flow of payments.

05:57:08.000 --> 05:57:23.000
Therefore, foreign trade policy for a good, floating, albeit adjustable currency exchange rate should be liberal. The next and last factor that I bring to our list is monetary and credit-money policy.

05:57:23.000 --> 05:57:37.000
As I said, the amount of money in the economy, in the end, affects inflation. On the other hand, in the medium and long term, it will certainly affect the currency exchange rate.

05:57:37.000 --> 05:57:54.000
And if, within the framework of credit-money policy, the government includes a printing press to reduce the deficit of the state budget, then just this excess money is thrown into two markets, the market of securities and the market of currency.

05:57:54.000 --> 05:58:10.000
And then, as we assume, the offer of a ruble will be higher than a dollar or higher than a euro, the currency exchange rate of the ruble begins to fall. This is another factor that affects the internal system as such.

05:58:10.000 --> 05:58:28.000
All these components that I listed can be considered in a foreign country. Why? Because all these six components will affect the exchange rate in relation to which we recognize the exchange rate of the Russian national currency.

05:58:28.000 --> 05:58:46.000
If the monetary authorities of the United States introduce a policy of reducing or increasing the interest rate, this is reflected in all the currencies that determine their floating exchange rate, including in relation to the US dollar.

05:58:46.000 --> 05:58:52.000
